a Marano || [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep66|Records & Wrecking Balls]]\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Can't Do It without You\" (''Austin & Ally'' Main Title)\n| Ross Lynch<br />Laura Marano || rowspan=\"2\" | [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep68|Buzzcuts & Beginnings]] || rowspan=\"5\" | ''[[Austin & Ally: Take It from the Top]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"No Place Like Home\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Laura Marano\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Play My Song\"\n| [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep76|Mini-Me's & Muffin Baskets]] \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Dance Like Nobody's Watching\"\n| [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep77|Dancers & Ditzes]]\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Take It from the Top\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Ross Lynch || [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep79|Comebacks & Crystal Balls]]\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Jump Back, Kiss Yourself\"\n| [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep84|Cap and Gown & Can't Be Found]] || rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Perfect Christmas\"\n| Ross Lynch<br />Laura Marano || [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep85|Santas & Surprises]]\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"[[You've Got a Friend#Other versions|You've Got a Friend]]\"\n| Raini Rodriguez ft.<br />''Austin & Ally'' cast || [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep86|Musicals & Moving On]]\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Two in a Million\"\n| Ross Lynch<br />Laura Marano || [[List of Austin & Ally episodes#ep87|Duets & Destiny]]\n|}\n\n== Broadcast ==\nThe series airs worldwide on Disney Channel. It aired as a preview in Canada alongside the original broadcast and premiered on January 20, 2012. It premiered in [[Singapore]] on March 3, 2012, and in Australia and [[New Zealand]] on March 23, 2012. In [[India]], the series premiered on [[Disney Channel (India)|Disney Channel]] on December 1, 2013, and on October 30, 2017 on [[Disney International HD]].{{citation needed|date=June 2019}} In the [[UK]] and [[Ireland]] the series aired a preview on March 30, 2012, and premiered on April 20, 2012. The series premiered on [[Disney Channel (Canada)|Disney Channel]] in Canada on September 1, 2015, with Raini Rodriguez and Calum Worthy introducing the series with special contests and events.\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Ratings ===\n{{Television season ratings\n| hide_timeslot     = y\n| hide_tv_season    = y\n| hide_rank         = y\n| hide_18_49_rank   = y\n| hide_18_49_rating = y\n\n| link1             = List of Austin & Ally episodes#Season 1 (2011\u201312)\n| episodes1         = 19<!-- should reflect the number of episodes that contribute to the average given in the last column -->\n| start1            = {{Start date|2011|12|2}}\n| end1              = {{End date|2012|9|9}}\n| startrating1      = 5.66<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2011/12/05/fridays-cable-ratings-gold-rush-holds-onto-demo-crown-279213/cable_20111202/|title=Friday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=December 5, 2011|access-date=December 4, 2017}}</ref>\n| endrating1        = 2.95<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/09/11/sundays-cable-ratings-kardashians-long-island-medium-top-demos-viewers-529014/cable_20120909/|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=September 11, 2012|access-date=December 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| viewers1          = {{decimals|{{#expr:((\n                      5.661 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 1: \"Rockers & Writers\" -->\n                      3.964 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 2: \"Kangaroos & Chaos\" -->\n                      3.398 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 3: \"Secrets & Songbooks\" -->\n                      2.991 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 4: \"Zaliens & Cloud Watchers\" -->\n                      2.807 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 5: \"Bloggers & Butterflies\" -->\n                      2.977 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 6: \"Tickets & Trashbags\" -->\n                      3.549 + <!-- raw ratings data from Episode 7: \"Managers & Meatballs\" -->