{"title_page": "A1 Ethniki Volleyball", "text_new": "{{Infobox Sports league\n| title          = A1 Ethniki Volleyball\n| current_season = 2018\u201319 Volleyleague (Greece)\n| logo           = Greek Volleyleague logo.jpg\n| pixels         = 190\n| caption        =\n| Formerly       =\n| sport          = Volleyball\n| founded        = 1935\n| fame           =\n| motto          =\n| promotion      =\n| relegation     = [[A2 Ethniki Volleyball]] (2nd Tier)\n| inaugural      =\n| domestic_cup   = [[Greek Volleyball Cup|Greek Cup]]<br />[[Greek Volleyball League Cup|League Cup]]\n| confed_cup     = [[CEV Champions League|Champions League]]<br />[[CEV Cup]]<br />[[CEV Challenge Cup|Challenge Cup]]\n| teams          = 10\n| country        = {{flag|Greece}}\n| continent      = {{flagicon|EU}} [[Europe]]\n| champion       = [[Olympiacos S.C.|Olympiacos]]\n| most_champs    = [[Olympiacos S.C.|Olympiacos]] <small>(29)</small>\n| qualification  =\n| folded         =\n| website        = [http://www.volleyball.gr/ www.volleyball.gr]\n| singles        =\n| ceo            =\n| Director       =\n| TV             = [[Hellenic Broadcasting Corporation|ERT]]\n| related_comps  =\n| Founder        =\n}}\n\nThe '''A1 Ethniki''' ({{lang-el|\u03911 \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03b7\u03b3\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b1}}), often referred to as the '''Greek Volleyball League''', is the highest professional [[volleyball]] league in [[Greece]]. It is run by the Hellenic Volleyball Federation. It is considered one of the top national leagues in European volleyball, as its clubs have made significant success in European competitions.\n\n==Current teams==\n{{Location map+ |Greece |width=400 |float=right |caption=Location of clubs for the 2018\u201319 Volley League season|places=\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=38.14 |long=23.787633 |label=[[AEK V.C.|AEK]]<br/>[[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos]]<br/>[[Kifissia AC|Kifissia]]|position=right}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=40.600069 |long=22.9695   |label=[[P.A.O.K. Thessaloniki V.C.|PAOK]]<br /> [[Iraklis Thessaloniki V.C.|Iraklis]]}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=37.92 |long=23.67   |label=[[Olympiacos S.C.|Olympiacos]]|position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat_deg=38|lat_min=0 |lon_deg=22 |lon_min=40 |label=[[Pamvochaikos]]|position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat_deg=37|lat_min=25 |lon_deg=24 |lon_min=55 |label=[[Foinikas Syros]]|position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat=41.1 |long=25.416667 |label=[[A.E. Komotini V.C.|A.E. Komotini]]|position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~ |Greece |lat_deg=40 |lat_min=50 |lon_deg=25 |lon_min=50 |label=[[Ethnikos Alexandroupoli V.C.|Ethnikos Alexandroupoli]]|position=bottom}}\n}}\nThe clubs for the '''2019\u201320''' season:\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Club\n!Home city\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[AS Elpis Ampelokipon|Elpis Ampelokipon]]'''||[[Ampelokipoi, Thessaloniki]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[Ethnikos Alexandroupolis V.C.|Ethnikos Alexandroupolis]]'''||[[Alexandroupolis]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[Foinikas Syros V.C.|Foinikas Syros]]'''||[[Ermoupolis]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[Iraklis V.C. (Thessaloniki)|Iraklis]]'''||[[Thessaloniki]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[Kifissia AC]]'''||[[Kifissia]], [[Athens]]\n|-\n|[[OFI Crete F.C.|OFI Crete]]\n|[[Heraklion]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[Olympiacos S.C.|Olympiacos]]'''||[[Piraeus]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[Pamvohaikos V.C.|Pamvohaikos]]'''||[[Vrahati]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[Panathinaikos V.C.|Panathinaikos]]'''||[[Athens]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''' [[P.A.O.K. V.C.|PAOK]]'''||[[Thessaloniki]]\n|}\n\n==Championship history==\n* ''1935\u201336 to 1967\u201368: '''Panhellenic Championship'''''\n* ''1968\u201369 to 1987\u201388: '''A Ethniki'''''\n* ''1988\u201389 to 2009\u201310: '''A1 Ethniki'''''\n* ''2010\u201311 to present: '''Volley League'''''\n\n==Title holders<ref>http://www.volleyleague.gr/index.php/component/k2/item/3506/o-polynikis-olympiakos-kai-o-protaris-paok</ref>==\n{{col-beg