onal footballers}}\n[[Vit\u0101lijs Astafjevs]] played for Latvia more than anyone else, with 167 caps from 1992 to 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/astafjevs-intl.html |title=Vitalijs Astafjevs \u2013 Century of International Appearances |work=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation |accessdate=1 June 2012 }}</ref> He also held the European record for 7 years for most matches played for the national team from 2009 until March 2017, when his record was beaten by [[Gianluigi Buffon]].<ref name=\"appearances\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/let-recintlp.html |title=Latvia \u2013 Record International Players |work=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation |accessdate=1 June 2012 }}</ref> Astafjevs has netted 16 times.<ref name=\"appearances\"/> [[Andris Va\u0146ins]] is the most capped active player for Latvia with 100 appearances, as of November 2019.<ref name=\"appearances\"/> [[M\u0101ris Verpakovskis]] is the nation's top goalscorer with 29 goals.<ref name=\"appearances\"/> Other high scorers include [[\u0112riks P\u0113tersons]] with 24 goals scored in the 1930s and [[Marians Pahars]] and [[Juris Laiz\u0101ns]], who both scored 15 goals each for Latvia.<ref name=\"appearances\"/>\n\n===Current squad===\nThe following players have been called up for the [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] matches against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] on 16 November 2019 and [[Austria national football team|Austria]] on 19 November 2019.<br />''All caps and goals as of 19 November 2019 after the match against [[Austria national football team|Austria]].\n{{nat fs g start|background=maroon|color=white}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=1|pos=GK|name=[[Andris Va\u0146ins]]|age={{birth date and age|1980|4|30|df=y}}|caps=100|goals=0|club=[[FC Z\u00fcrich|Z\u00fcrich]]|clubnat=SUI}} \n{{nat fs g player|no=23|pos=GK|name=[[P\u0101vels \u0160teinbors]]|other=[[Captain (association football)|Captain]]|age={{birth date and age|1985|9|21|df=y}}|caps=12|goals=0|club=[[Arka Gdynia]]|clubnat=POL}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=12|pos=GK|name=[[Roberts Ozols (footballer)|Roberts Ozols]]|age={{birth date and age|1995|9|10|df=y}}|caps=0|goals=0|club=[[Riga FC|Riga]]|clubnat=LAT}}\n{{nat fs break|background=maroon}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=2|pos=DF|name=[[Vit\u0101lijs Maksimenko]]|age={{birth date and age|1990|12|8|df=y}}|caps=51|goals=1|club=[[Omiya Ardija]]|clubnat=JPN}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=4|pos=DF|name=[[Kaspars Dubra]]|age={{Birth date and age|1990|12|20|df=yes}}|caps=36|goals=2|club=[[FC Oleksandriya|Oleksandriya]]|clubnat=UKR}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=16|pos=DF|name=[[Igors Tarasovs]]|age={{Birth date and age|1988|2|16|df=yes}}|caps=35|goals=2|club=[[Kaposv\u00e1ri R\u00e1k\u00f3czi FC|Kaposv\u00e1r]]|clubnat=HUN}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=19|pos=DF|name=[[Vit\u0101lijs Jagodinskis]]|age={{Birth date and age|1992|2|28|df=yes}}|caps=31|goals=0|club=[[Valmieras FK|Valmiera]]|clubnat=LAT}} \n{{nat fs g player|no=3|pos=DF|name=[[M\u0101rcis O\u0161s]]|age={{Birth date and age|1991|7|25|df=yes}}|caps=11|goals=1|club=[[Neuch\u00e2tel Xamax]]|clubnat=SUI}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=8|pos=DF|name=[[Raivis Jurkovskis]]|age={{Birth date and age|1996|12|7|df=y}}|caps=7|goals=0|club=[[FK Liep\u0101ja|Liep\u0101ja]]|clubnat=LAT}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=17|pos=DF|name=[[Antonijs \u010cernomordijs]]|age={{Birth date and age|1996|9|26|df=y}}|caps=4|goals=0|club=[[Riga FC|Riga]]|clubnat=LVA}}\n{{nat fs break|background=maroon}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=5|pos=MF|name=[[O\u013cegs Laiz\u0101ns]]|age={{birth date and age|1987|3|28|df=y}}|caps=54|goals=0|club=[[Riga FC|Riga]]|clubnat=LAT}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=7|pos=MF|name=[[Ritvars Rugins]]|age={{Birth date and age|1989|10|17|df=yes}}|caps=35|goals=0|club=[[Riga FC|Riga]]|clubnat=LAT}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=6|pos=MF|name=[[Vladimirs Kame\u0161s]]|age={{Birth date and age|1988|10|28|df=yes}}|caps=24|goals=2|club=[[FC Chayka Peschanokopskoye|Chayka Peschanokopskoye]]|clubnat=RUS}}\n{{nat fs g player|no